dslRuleAfterChange:
A hypothetical DSL syntax might look like:

// Ensure correctly sized array is passed to beginToCompile
beginToCompile($arrayVar, $bindingKeys)
=> {
    org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.env.ICompilationUnit[] tempArray = new org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.env.ICompilationUnit[$countVar];
    System.arraycopy($arrayVar, 0, tempArray, 0, $countVar);
    beginToCompile(tempArray, $bindingKeys);
}
;;

However, the 'length' variable (used to decide 'count < length') in the original context is not directly part of the matched pattern, so capturing it would also be a challenge.

A hypothetical DSL syntax might look like:

// Optimize array copy for beginToCompile if array is already correctly sized
beginToCompile($arrayVar, $bindingKeys)
=> {
    if ($countVar < $lengthVar) {
        org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.env.ICompilationUnit[] tempArray = new org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.env.ICompilationUnit[$countVar];
        System.arraycopy($arrayVar, 0, tempArray, 0, $countVar);
        $arrayVar = tempArray;
    }
    beginToCompile($arrayVar, $bindingKeys);
}
;;

As in the previous commit, capturing '$lengthVar' from the surrounding context would also be a challenge.

dslRule:
new java.lang.String($str.substring($args$)) :: sourceVersionGE(8)
=> $str.substring($args$)
;;

new java.lang.String($str) :: sourceVersionGE(8) && instanceof($str, "java.lang.String")
=> $str
;;

new java.lang.String($sb.toString()) :: sourceVersionGE(8) && (instanceof($sb, "java.lang.StringBuilder") || instanceof($sb, "java.lang.StringBuffer"))
=> $sb.toString()
;;
